(64, 4, 12, '<p>(1) Nilai tukar rupiah terhadap dollar AS pada penutupan  perdagangan di pasar spot pada Kamis (30/1/2020) mengalami pelemahan. (2) Mengutip data <em>Bloomberg</em>, rupiah ditutup pada level Rp 13.657 atau melemah 0,17 persen dibandingkan sebelumnya di posisi Rp 13.634 per dollar AS. (3) Menurut Direktur PT TRFX Garuda Berjangka, Ibrahim, kondisi total yang terus tak menentu. (4) Hal ini mengharuskan pemerintah dan BI harus memperkuat stabilitas ekonominya. (5) “Dengan cara melakukan strategi baruan kebijakan moneter maupun yang lainnya bisa meningkatkan kepercayaan pasar terhadap perekonomian dalam negeri sehingga arus modal kembali masuk,” kata Ibrahim. (6) Di samping itu Bank Indonesia harus kembali menurunkan suku bunga acuan guna untuk menjaga pertumbuhan ekonomi agar sesuai dengan target yang diinginkan yakni 5,1 persen sampai 5,2 persen. (7) Sebelumnya BI juga melakukan intervensi di pasar valas dan obligasi untuk perdagangan DNDF yang mana perdagangan tersebut sudah aktif  bertransaksi sejak pagi. (8) Intervensi yang dilakukan sore ini belum bisa menguatkan rupiah.  (9) Di sisi lain, pelemahan rupiah juga terjadi sebagai akibat dari merebaknya wabah virus corona di China. (10) Hasil riset S&P menunjukkan virus corona akan memangkas pertumbuhan ekonomi China sebesar 1,2 persen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Diadaptasi dari <em>https://www.kompas.com> tag > ekonomi)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>12. Dalam teks tersebut keberpihakan penulis ditujukan kepada siapa?</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Investor</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Masyarakat</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pemerintah AS</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>BI dan pemerintah</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pemerintah China</span></span></span></p>', 4, '<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Keberpihakan penulis adalah kecenderungan penulis untuk memberikan dukungan pada pihak apa atau mana yang diungkapkan dalam sebuah tajuk rencana.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Dalam teks tersebut penulis berpihak kepada pemerintah dan Bank Indonesia yang telah mengeluarkan kebijakan agar nilai tukar rupiah tidak melemah, meski sudah berusaha namun belum ada hasilnya.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>', '2020-12-08 02:34:11', '2020-12-08 02:34:11'),
(65, 3, 11, '<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(1) Survei berjudul \"International Public Opinion Survey on Cancer 2020: What people feel, think, and believe about cancer today\" yang dilakukan oleh Union for International Cancer Control (UICC) menunjukkan perbedaan yang jelas antara masyarakat kelompok ekonomi tinggi dan rendah dalam hal pengetahuan dan kesadaran akan faktor resiko kanker. (2) Survei ini dilakukan terhadap 15.472 orang dewasa di 20 negara untuk peringatan Hari Kanker Sedunia ke-20.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(3) Hasil survei menunjukkan, masyarakat kelas ekonomi menengah ke atas ditemukan memiliki kesadaran dan pemahaman yang lebih tinggi tentang kanker dibandingkan masyarakat kelas ekonomi menengah ke bawah. (4) Selain itu, hasil survei ini menemukan beberapa faktor resiko yang paling &#39;populer&#39; di tengah masyarakat. (5) Kebiasaan merokok (63%), paparan sinar ultraviolet (54%), dan paparan asap rokok dari orang lain (50%) merupakan tiga faktor resiko yang paling dikenali dan disadari. (6) ... faktor resiko seperti kurang aktivitas fisik atau olahraga (28%), paparan virus atau bakteri tertentu (28%), dan kelebihan berat badan (29%) menjadi yang paling tidak &#39;populer&#39; di tengah masyarakat.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(7) Masyarakat dari golongan rumah tangga berpendapatan rendah ditemukan lebih tidak mengenali faktor resiko kanker daripada mereka yang berasal dari rumah tangga berpendapatan tinggi. (8) Tren ini juga ditemukan terjadi di antara orang dengan tingkat pendidikan tinggi (setara universitas) dengan yang rendah. (9) Sementara beberapa mengaku memahami faktor resiko kanker, beberapa lainnya justru mengaku sama sekali tak tahu-menahu. (10) Dalam kategori ini, masyarakat dengan pendapatan rendah menjadi kelompok terbesar (9%), diikuti oleh masyarakat menengah (6%), dan masyarakat menengah ke atas (4%). (11) Selain kurang mengenali faktor resiko, mereka dengan pendidikan dan tingkat ekonomi rendah juga ditemukan tidak proaktif dalam mengambil langkah-langkah demi mengurangi resiko kanker.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(12) Dari hasil survei ini, UICC menyerukan agar pemerintah setiap negara dapat memprioritaskan peningkatan kesadaran masyarakat terhadap kanker melalui kebijakan dan pendidikan kesehatan yang progresif. (13) Pemerintah juga diminta fokus pada kelompok masyarakat kelas menengah ke bawah. (14) Selain itu, pemerintah juga diminta untuk menerapkan kebijakan demi mengurangi konsumsi produk penyebab kanker seperti tembakau serta makanan dan minuman bergula.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(Diadaptasi dari https://www.cnnindonesia.com/gaya-hidup/20200204112310-255-471434/survei-masyarakat-menengah-bawah-tak-sadar-resiko-kanker)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed> </p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n <li xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pada kalimat nomor berapa terdapat kesalahan penggunaan tanda baca?</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>', '<p>2</p>', '<p>3</p>', '<p>4</p>', '<p>5</p>', '<p>6</p>', 2, '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Kunci Jawabannya adalah </span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><strong>(B)</strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pembahasan</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pada kalimat (3) tidak perlu koma sesudah kata menunjukkan.</span></span></span></p>', '2020-12-08 02:34:18', '2020-12-08 02:34:18'),
(66, 6, 4, '<p>Produk utama dari reaksi kimia antara 2 – metil – 1 – propena dengan HBr adalah….</p>', '<p>1 – bromo – 2 – metil propana</p>', '<p>2 – bromo – 2 – metil propana</p>', '<p>​​​​​​2 – bromo – 1 – metil propana</p>', '<p>2 – metil – 2 – bromo propana</p>', '<p>2 – metil – 1 – bromo propana</p>', 2, '<p>2 – metil – 1 – propena + HBr<sub>  →</sub></p>\r\n\r\n<p>                                                         Br</p>\r\n\r\n<p>                                                         |</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CH2 = C – CH3 + HBr  à  CH3 –  C – CH3</p>\r\n\r\n<p>            |                                           |</p>\r\n\r\n<p>            CH3                                     CH3</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>                                          2 – bromo – 2 – metil propana</strong></p>', '2020-12-08 02:34:20', '2020-12-08 02:34:42'),
(67, 5, 13, '<p>Si Lisa dan Si Mirna memiliki pekerjaan sebagai asisten rumah tangga. Waktu yang dibutuhkan oleh Si Lisa dalam mencuci piring adalah 30 menit, sedangkan waktu yang dibutuhkan oleh Si Mirna adalah 60 menit. Jika Si Lisa dan Si Mirna bekerja bersama-sama dalam mencuci piring tersebut, maka waktu yang dibutuhkan adalah …</p>', '<p>15 Menit</p>', '<p>20 Menit</p>', '<p>30 Menit</p>', '<p>45 Menit</p>', '<p>60 Menit</p>', 2, '<p><img alt=\"IMG_256\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/gPIAojy-r9ySJtwVaQRDliBxUWq0X5ioyzOZyZxIrlPiRodVQ-Pl6ctEnkgzFFUpMnqEY9eCjAIZBtuo8jz7VXecE7oKePPm31V7MNGg-n-oix-htqDnXAMKup5ohvnK65Ml3Lw\"></p>', '2020-12-08 02:37:29', '2020-12-08 02:39:12'),
(68, 4, 12, '<p xss=removed>The virus causing illness in Wuhan is a novel coronavirus – a member of the coronavirus family that has never been encountered before. Like other coronaviruses, it is zoonotic, meaning it is transmitted between animals and people. New and troubling viruses usually originate in animal hosts. Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) and Middle Eastern Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) are both caused by coronaviruses that came from animals. Although MERS is believed to be transmitted to humans from dromedaries (Arabian camels), the original hosts for both coronaviruses were probably bats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed>The Wuhan novel coronavirus causes pneumonia. Those who have fallen ill are reported to suffer coughs, fever and breathing difficulties. In severe cases there can be organ failure. As this is viral pneumonia, antibiotics are of no use. The antiviral drugs we have against flu will not work. If people are admitted to hospital, they may get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids. Recovery will depend on the strength of their immune system. Many of those who have died were already in poor health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed>Human to human transmission has been confirmed by China’s national health commission. Many of those infected either worked or frequently shopped in the Huanan seafood wholesale market in the centre of the Chinese city, which also sold live and newly slaughtered animals. As of 30 January, the death toll in China stands at 170, with more than 7,500 confirmed cases of infections. In the past week, the number of confirmed infections has more than tripled and cases have been found in 13 provinces, as well as the municipalities of Beijing, Shanghai, Chongqing and Tianjin. The virus has been confirmed outside mainland China, in Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, and in Japan, Nepal, Singapore, South Korea, Thailand, the US, and Vietnam. Two members of one family have been confirmed to have the virus in the UK, after more than 160 were tested and found negative. The actual number to have contracted the virus could be far higher as people with mild symptoms may not have been detected. Modelling by World Health Organization (WHO) experts at Imperial College London suggests there could be as many as 100,000 cases, with uncertainty putting the margins between 30,000 and 200,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed>(Adapted from https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/31/what-is-coronavirus-symptoms-wuhan-china-how-worried-doctor)</p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed>13. What is the main idea of the passage?</p>', '<p>The virus found in Wuhan has been recognize before.</p>', '<p>Animals usually become the hosts of troubling viruses.</p>', '<p>A disease outbreak in Wuhan is caused by unknown virus.</p>', '<p>SARS, MERS, and illness in Wuhan are caused by the same virus.</p>', '<p>Virus causing illness in Wuhan is in the same family as MERS and SARS.</p>', 5, '<p>Jawaban E dijelaskan dalam kalimat “The virus causing illness in Wuhan is a novel coronavirus – a member of the coronavirus family …” dan “Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) and Middle Eastern Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) are both caused by coronaviruses …”</p>', '2020-12-08 02:38:06', '2020-12-08 07:22:03'),
(69, 4, 12, '<p>The virus causing illness in Wuhan is a novel coronavirus – a member of the coronavirus family that has never been encountered before. Like other coronaviruses, it is zoonotic, meaning it is transmitted between animals and people. New and troubling viruses usually originate in animal hosts. Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) and Middle Eastern Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) are both caused by coronaviruses that came from animals. Although MERS is believed to be transmitted to humans from dromedaries (Arabian camels), the original hosts for both coronaviruses were probably bats.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Wuhan novel coronavirus causes pneumonia. Those who have fallen ill are reported to suffer coughs, fever and breathing difficulties. In severe cases there can be organ failure. As this is viral pneumonia, antibiotics are of no use. The antiviral drugs we have against flu will not work. If people are admitted to hospital, they may get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids. Recovery will depend on the strength of their immune system. Many of those who have died were already in poor health.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Human to human transmission has been confirmed by China’s national health commission. Many of those infected either worked or frequently shopped in the Huanan seafood wholesale market in the centre of the Chinese city, which also sold live and newly slaughtered animals. As of 30 January, the death toll in China stands at 170, with more than 7,500 confirmed cases of infections. In the past week, the number of confirmed infections has more than tripled and cases have been found in 13 provinces, as well as the municipalities of Beijing, Shanghai, Chongqing and Tianjin. The virus has been confirmed outside mainland China, in Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, and in Japan, Nepal, Singapore, South Korea, Thailand, the US, and Vietnam. Two members of one family have been confirmed to have the virus in the UK, after more than 160 were tested and found negative. The actual number to have contracted the virus could be far higher as people with mild symptoms may not have been detected. Modelling by World Health Organization (WHO) experts at Imperial College London suggests there could be as many as 100,000 cases, with uncertainty putting the margins between 30,000 and 200,000.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Adapted from https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/jan/31/what-is-coronavirus-symptoms-wuhan-china-how-worried-doctor)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>14. The sentence ‘If people are admitted to hospital, they may get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids’ in paragraph 2 can be restated as …</p>', '<p>the people are not admitted to hospital because they do not get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids</p>', '<p>the people do not get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids although they are admitted to hospital</p>', '<p>the people probably get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids when they are admitted to hospital</p>', '<p>the people do not get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids since they are admitted to hospital</p>', '<p>the people are not admitted to hospital so they get support for their lungs and other organs as well as fluids</p>', 3, '<p>Kalimat yang dikutip dari paragraf 2 adalah Conditional Sentence Type 1, sehingga dapat dinyatakan sebagai kemungkinan (probably, possibly, perhaps)</p>', '2020-12-08 02:39:59', '2020-12-08 07:23:22'),
