(92, 7, 1, '<p>Akar-akar persamaan 2x<sup>2</sup>+8x+m = 0 adalah x<sub>1</sub> dan x<sub>2</sub>. Jika 7x<sub>1</sub>-x<sub>2</sub>=20 makanilai m = ….</p>', '<p>-24</p>', '<p>-12</p>', '<p>12</p>', '<p>18</p>', '<p>20</p>', 1, '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Akar-akar persamaan 2x<sup>2</sup>+8x+m = 0 adalah x<sub>1</sub> dan x<sub>2</sub>. Jika 7x<sub>1</sub>-x<sub>2</sub>=20 maka nilai m =...</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>X<sub>1</sub> + X<sub>2</sub> = - b/a</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><img xss=removed>  X<sub>1</sub> + X<sub>2</sub> = - 4 ....(1)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>7X<sub>1</sub>  - X<sub>2</sub> =20....(2).</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Dari (1) + (2)  diperoleh : 8X<sub>1</sub> = 16 dan X<sub>1</sub> = 2 sehingga X<sub>2</sub> = - 6 </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>X<sub>1</sub> .X<sub>2</sub> = c/a</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><img xss=removed>  X<sub>1</sub> . X<sub>2</sub> = m/2</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><img xss=removed>  2.-6 = m/2</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><img xss=removed></span></span> <span xss=removed><span xss=removed>X<sub>1</sub> . X<sub>2</sub> = - 24 </span></span></p>', '2020-12-08 02:51:55', '2020-12-08 03:02:28'),
(93, 4, 12, '<p>It is important to understand that bacterial and viral infections must be treated differently. While bacteria and viruses can both cause mild to serious infections, they are different from each other. Misusing antibiotics to treat viral infections contributes to the problem of antibiotic resistance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bacteria and viruses are too tiny to be seen by the naked eye, can cause similar symptoms and are often spread in the same way, but that’s where the similarities end.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A bacterium is a single, but complex, cell. It can survive on its own, inside or outside the body. Most bacteria aren’t harmful. In fact, we have many bacteria on and inside our body, especially in the gut to help digest food.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Viruses are smaller and are not cells. Unlike bacteria, they need a host such as a human or animal to multiply. Viruses cause infections by entering and multiplying inside the host’s healthy cells.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is important to know whether bacteria or viruses cause an infection, because the treatments differ. Examples of bacterial infections include whooping cough, strep throat, ear infection and urinary tract infection (UTI). Viral infections include the common cold, flu, most coughs and bronchitis, chickenpox and HIV/AIDS.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It can be difficult to know what causes an infection, because viral and bacterial infections can cause similar symptoms. Your doctor may need a sample of your urine, stool and blood for a ‘culture’ test to have the bugs identified under a microscope.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Doctors usually treat bacterial infections with antibiotics. They either kill bacteria or stop them multiplying. But since antibiotic resistance is a growing problem, antibiotics may be prescribed only for serious bacterial infections.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The treatment of viral infections can include managing symptoms, such as honey for coughs and warm fluids like chicken soup for oral hydration, paracetamol to relieve fever, stopping viral reproduction using antiviral medicines, such as medicines for HIV/AIDS and cold sores, and preventing infection in the first place, such as vaccines for flu and hepatitis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>(Adapted from https://www.healthdirect.gov.au/bacterial-vs-viral-infection)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>18. The sentence “…, but that’s where the similarities end” stated in the passage means that …</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>there are similarities between bacteria and viruses</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>there similarities between bacteria and viruses have to be ended</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>there similarities between bacteria and viruses have to be ended</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>viral and bacterial infections can cause their similarities come to an end</span></span></span></p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>to end the similarities between bacteria and viruses needs experts’ researches</span></span></span></p>', 3, '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Pernyataan “tetapi di situlah persamaan itu berakhir” bermakna bahwa kesamaan bakteri dan virus adalah hanya sama-sama sangat kecil untuk dilihat dengan mata telanjang, keduanya dapat menyebabkan gejala penyakit yang sama, dan sering menyebar dengan cara yang sama. Lebih jauh lagi, kalimat tersebut secara tersirat menunjukkan adanya perbedaan antara virus dan bakteri.</span></span></span></p>', '2020-12-08 02:54:31', '2020-12-08 02:54:31'),
(94, 3, 11, '<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(1) Survei berjudul \"International Public Opinion Survey on Cancer 2020: What people feel, think, and believe about cancer today\" yang dilakukan oleh Union for International Cancer Control (UICC) menunjukkan perbedaan yang jelas antara masyarakat kelompok ekonomi tinggi dan rendah dalam hal pengetahuan dan kesadaran akan faktor resiko kanker. (2) Survei ini dilakukan terhadap 15.472 orang dewasa di 20 negara untuk peringatan Hari Kanker Sedunia ke-20.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(3) Hasil survei menunjukkan, masyarakat kelas ekonomi menengah ke atas ditemukan memiliki kesadaran dan pemahaman yang lebih tinggi tentang kanker dibandingkan masyarakat kelas ekonomi menengah ke bawah. (4) Selain itu, hasil survei ini menemukan beberapa faktor resiko yang paling &#39;populer&#39; di tengah masyarakat. (5) Kebiasaan merokok (63%), paparan sinar ultraviolet (54%), dan paparan asap rokok dari orang lain (50%) merupakan tiga faktor resiko yang paling dikenali dan disadari. (6) ... faktor resiko seperti kurang aktivitas fisik atau olahraga (28%), paparan virus atau bakteri tertentu (28%), dan kelebihan berat badan (29%) menjadi yang paling tidak &#39;populer&#39; di tengah masyarakat.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(7) Masyarakat dari golongan rumah tangga berpendapatan rendah ditemukan lebih tidak mengenali faktor resiko kanker daripada mereka yang berasal dari rumah tangga berpendapatan tinggi. (8) Tren ini juga ditemukan terjadi di antara orang dengan tingkat pendidikan tinggi (setara universitas) dengan yang rendah. (9) Sementara beberapa mengaku memahami faktor resiko kanker, beberapa lainnya justru mengaku sama sekali tak tahu-menahu. (10) Dalam kategori ini, masyarakat dengan pendapatan rendah menjadi kelompok terbesar (9%), diikuti oleh masyarakat menengah (6%), dan masyarakat menengah ke atas (4%). (11) Selain kurang mengenali faktor resiko, mereka dengan pendidikan dan tingkat ekonomi rendah juga ditemukan tidak proaktif dalam mengambil langkah-langkah demi mengurangi resiko kanker.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(12) Dari hasil survei ini, UICC menyerukan agar pemerintah setiap negara dapat memprioritaskan peningkatan kesadaran masyarakat terhadap kanker melalui kebijakan dan pendidikan kesehatan yang progresif. (13) Pemerintah juga diminta fokus pada kelompok masyarakat kelas menengah ke bawah. (14) Selain itu, pemerintah juga diminta untuk menerapkan kebijakan demi mengurangi konsumsi produk penyebab kanker seperti tembakau serta makanan dan minuman bergula.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>(Diadaptasi dari https://www.cnnindonesia.com/gaya-hidup/20200204112310-255-471434/survei-masyarakat-menengah-bawah-tak-sadar-resiko-kanker)</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n <li xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Apa kelemahan yang ada dalam paragraf 3?</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>', '<p><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Penggunaan kata </span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><em>dari pada</em></span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> pada kalimat (7)</span></span></span></p>', '<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Penggunaan kata </span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><em>di antara</em></span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed> pada kalimat (8)</span></span></span></p>', '<p xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed>Penggunaan kata </span></span></span><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><span xss=removed><em>